# Color System Reference

The color system is defined in [src/css/foundation/colors.css](mdc:src/css/foundation/colors.css) and follows a structured approach with primitives, scales, semantic aliases, and utility classes.

## Color Variable Structure

### Primitive Colors
```css
--color-primary-signal-orange: #FC5C50
--color-primary-sky-blue: #00B2FF
--color-neutral-black: #181B25
--color-neutral-eggshell: #EBE5D8
--color-neutral-off-white: #F6F3EB
--color-neutral-white: #FDFDFD
--color-white: #FFFFFF
```

### Color Scales
Each color has a 9-step scale (100-900):
- Blue: `--color-blue-100` through `--color-blue-900`
- Red: `--color-red-100` through `--color-red-900`
- Green: `--color-green-100` through `--color-green-900`
- Orange: `--color-orange-100` through `--color-orange-900`
- Gray: `--color-gray-100` through `--color-gray-900`

### Semantic Color Aliases
Use semantic names instead of literal colors:
```css
--color-foundation-primary: var(--color-blue-700)
--color-foundation-secondary: var(--color-neutral-off-white)
--color-foundation-accent-a: var(--color-primary-sky-blue)
--color-foundation-accent-b: var(--color-primary-signal-orange)
--color-foundation-critical: var(--color-red-700)
--color-foundation-warning: var(--color-orange-700)
--color-foundation-success: var(--color-green-700)
```

## Utility Classes

